data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bhc1665702738396.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bhc1665702738396.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bhc1665702738396.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bhc1665702738396\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configure the TLS Connector with a Pre-Shared Key\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">It is relatively easy to configure Uniface to use TLS using a pre-shared key, but it is not recommended for a production environment.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__context_w7037ab1b5b1_w7038ab1b5_w7039ab1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__note_w7043ab1b5b1b1_w7044ab1b5b1_w7045ab1b5_w7046ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> It is recommended that you used certificate-protected TLS connections.\n            For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"trs1665702548192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/trs1665702548192.html\" title=\"To configure the TLS connector to use certificates to secure the connection and encrypt the data, you must enable server verification. If required, you can also enable client verification.\">Configure the TLS Connector to Use Certificates</a>. </div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__topic_d32648e1_d32649e1_d32650e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32651e1_d32652e1_d32653e1\">The following steps explain how to configure the Uniface Router-client connection to use TLS on port 13002.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16841e1_d16842e1_d16843e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32654e1_d32655e1_d32656e1\">Stop the Uniface Router and all the applications\n               that access it. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ztf1665702528456.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ztf1665702528456.html\" title=\"There may be occasions when you need to stop and restart the Uniface Router for system administrative purposes.\">Stop and Start the Uniface Router</a>. </div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16844e1_d16845e1_d16846e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32657e1_d32658e1_d32659e1\">In the <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span>file, set\n               the TLS connector option <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">shared_key</span> in the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TLS_PARAMS</span> setting:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;urouter.asn\n[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nUSYS$TLS_PARAMS shared_key=th1s Is my s*cret pHrase</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16847e1_d16848e1_d16849e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Restart the Uniface Router with the TLS port.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16850e1_d16851e1_d16852e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32660e1_d32661e1_d32662e1\">On Windows, remove the\n                        <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter</span> service and reinstall it using\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">TLS:</code>.  </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__ol_b2k_2bn_qcc\" type=\"i\">\n<li class=\"li\">Remove the <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter</span> service using the command\n                           line urouter <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/rem=\"ServiceName\"</span>. For example:<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104bhc1665702738396_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__codeblock_ky3_5bn_qcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">D:\\uniface\\common\\bin\\urouter /rem \"Uniface urouter\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div></li>\n<li class=\"li\">Reinstall it using the same command line used before, but specify the\n                           TLS: port. For example:<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104bhc1665702738396_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__codeblock_q3z_xbn_qcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">urouter.exe /inst \"Uniface urouter\" tls:+13002</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hjn1665702738471.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hjn1665702738471.html\" title=\"Executable file for the Uniface Router.\">urouter</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16859e1_d16860e1_d16861e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">On Unix, if you are starting the Uniface Router from the command line or a shell script:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">urouter tls:+13002</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16862e1_d16863e1_d16864e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the assignment file of the client applications that should communicate with the Uniface Router using TLS.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16865e1_d16866e1_d16867e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the TLS connector option <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">shared_key</span> with the same pre-shared key as the Uniface Router. For example::\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;client.asn\n[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nUSYS$TLS_PARAMS shared_key=th1s Is my s*cret pHrase</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16868e1_d16869e1_d16870e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32663e1_d32664e1_d32665e1\">Replace <code class=\"ph codeph\">TCP:</code> with\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">TLS:</code> in the connection string of all paths that lead to the\n                     specific Uniface Router. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">This can include database paths, and the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_NET</span> and\n                           <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DNP</span> settings. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; client.asn\n[PATHS]\n; path to the Uniface Server for an SQL Lite database:\n$DBMS=TLS:ABC_host+13002|user|password|SLESERVER \n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16871e1_d16872e1_d16873e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Restart the client application to have the new configuration take effect.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__result_w7040ab1b5b5_w7041ab1b5_w7042ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32666e1_d32667e1_d32668e1\">After successful deployment of TLS, the firewall can be configured to block the incoming data to the TCP port of the Uniface Router and only forward incoming data over the newly configured TLS port of the Uniface Router.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"example\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__example_ewl_gcn_qcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d228815e247\">Securing the Shared Key</h2>\n<div class=\"div postreq\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__topic_d32675e1_d32676e1_d32677e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32678e1_d32679e1_d32680e1\">A pre-shared key can potentially be read by a\n               hacker who has gained read access to your assignment files, so you should take\n               precautions to prevent this:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__ul_erm_3cn_qcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16874e1_d16875e1_d16876e1\">Use Pathscrambler to encrypt the key in your\n                  assignment files. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jbd1665702548027.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jbd1665702548027.html\" title=\"The Pathscrambler is command-line utility for encrypting sensitive information and values in assignment files and login strings. These may be used in assignment files, servlet settings, the open ProcScript statement and the /log (login) command line switch. Uniface automatically decrypts any data that has been encrypted with the Pathscrambler.\">Pathscrambler</a> and\n                     <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hot1665702522640.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hot1665702522640.html\" title=\"Use the Pathscrambler to encrypt logon strings and other sensitive information in assignment files, servlet settings, the open ProcScript command, and the /log (login) command line switch.\">Encrypting Paths and Other Sensitive Data Using PathScrambler</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__li_d16877e1_d16878e1_d16879e1\">Restrict <code class=\"ph codeph\">read</code> access to the\n                  user account under which the Uniface executable runs (for example,\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface</span> for client applications,\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">userver</span> for Uniface Servers, and\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter</span> for Uniface Router). </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bhc1665702738396__p_d32681e1_d32682e1_d32683e1\">Certificates provide better protection than pre-shared\n            keys. Once you have TLS working with pre-shared keys, consider whether some TLS\n            connections should use certificate authentication. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"trs1665702548192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/trs1665702548192.html\" title=\"To configure the TLS connector to use certificates to secure the connection and encrypt the data, you must enable server verification. If required, you can also enable client verification.\">Configure the TLS Connector to Use Certificates</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configure the TLS Connector with a Pre-Shared Key Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configure the TLS Connector with a Pre-Shared Key It is relatively easy to configure Uniface to use TLS using a pre-shared key, but it is not recommended for a production environment. Note: It is recommended that you used certificate-protected TLS connections. For more information, see Configure the TLS Connector to Use Certificates . The following steps explain how to configure the Uniface Router-client connection to use TLS on port 13002. Stop the Uniface Router and all the applications that access it. For more information, see Stop and Start the Uniface Router . In the urouter.asn file, set the TLS connector option shared_key in the USYS$TLS_PARAMS setting: ;urouter.asn [DRIVER_SETTINGS] USYS$TLS_PARAMS shared_key=th1s Is my s*cret pHrase Copy Restart the Uniface Router with the TLS port. On Windows, remove the urouter service and reinstall it using TLS: . Remove the urouter service using the command line urouter /rem=\"ServiceName\" . For example: Explain this code D:\\uniface\\common\\bin\\urouter /rem \"Uniface urouter\" Copy Reinstall it using the same command line used before, but specify the TLS: port. For example: Explain this code urouter.exe /inst \"Uniface urouter\" tls:+13002 Copy For more information, see urouter . On Unix, if you are starting the Uniface Router from the command line or a shell script: urouter tls:+13002 Copy Edit the assignment file of the client applications that should communicate with the Uniface Router using TLS. Set the TLS connector option shared_key with the same pre-shared key as the Uniface Router. For example:: ;client.asn [DRIVER_SETTINGS] USYS$TLS_PARAMS shared_key=th1s Is my s*cret pHrase Copy Replace TCP: with TLS: in the connection string of all paths that lead to the specific Uniface Router. This can include database paths, and the $DEFAULT_NET and $DNP settings. For example: ; client.asn [PATHS] ; path to the Uniface Server for an SQL Lite database: $DBMS=TLS:ABC_host+13002|user|password|SLESERVER Copy Restart the client application to have the new configuration take effect. After successful deployment of TLS, the firewall can be configured to block the incoming data to the TCP port of the Uniface Router and only forward incoming data over the newly configured TLS port of the Uniface Router. Securing the Shared Key A pre-shared key can potentially be read by a hacker who has gained read access to your assignment files, so you should take precautions to prevent this: Use Pathscrambler to encrypt the key in your assignment files. For more information, see Pathscrambler and Encrypting Paths and Other Sensitive Data Using PathScrambler . Restrict read access to the user account under which the Uniface executable runs (for example, uniface for client applications, userver for Uniface Servers, and urouter for Uniface Router). Certificates provide better protection than pre-shared keys. Once you have TLS working with pre-shared keys, consider whether some TLS connections should use certificate authentication. For more information, see Configure the TLS Connector to Use Certificates . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}